    public class FibreChannelSession
extends Object
implements Serializable
    FibreChannelSession contains information about each Fibre Channel session that is visible to the cluster and what target ports it is visible on.

      • FibreChannelSession

        @Since(value="7.0")
public FibreChannelSession(String initiatorWWPN,
                         Long nodeID,
                         Long serviceID,
                         String targetWWPN,
                         Long volumeAccessGroupID)
        FibreChannelSession contains information about each Fibre Channel session that is visible to the cluster and what target ports it is visible on.
        Parameters:
        initiatorWWPN - [required] The WWPN of the initiator which is logged into the target port.
        nodeID - [required] The node owning the Fibre Channel session.
        serviceID - [required] The service ID of the FService owning this Fibre Channel session
        targetWWPN - [required] The WWPN of the target port involved in this session.
        volumeAccessGroupID - [required] The ID of the volume access group to which the initiatorWWPN belongs. If not in a volume access group, the value will be null.
        Since:
        7.0
